7 SUBCOMMITTEE RECOMMENDATION
8 An Act relating to Home and Community-based programs;
directing the Department of Human Services to update
9 and maintain certain website; requiring Department to
include a rating system, inspection reports,
10 substantiated complaints, and administrator
information; mandating annual updates from agencies;
11 providing for codification; and providing an
effective date.
12
13
14
15 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
16 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
17 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-1975 of Title 63, unless there
18 is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
19 A. The Department of Human Services shall update and maintain
20 its Provider Search website that locates agencies that provide
21 services for the following Home and Community-based programs:
22 1. Advantage Waiver;
23 2. Living Choice;
24 3. Medically Fragile Waiver; and
Req. No. 16182 Page 1

1 4. State Plan Personal Care (SPPC).
2 B. The website shall also include:
3 1. A rating system established by the Department or another
4 accredited licensing agency;
5 2. Inspection reports;
6 3. Substantiated complaints;
7 4. Administrator information; and
8 5. A link to the State Department of Health to be able to
9 report an issue with an agency.
10 C. The Department shall require agencies to update information
11 on the website annually.
12 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2026.
